format: This data frame contains the following columns:

parameters.Bodywt:
a numeric vector consisting of the body weights (in kg) 
of five
different primates
parameters.Brainwt: a numeric vector consisting of the corresponding brain weights (in g)

title: Primate Body and Brain Weights
description:
Description
A subset of Animals data frame from the MASS library.
It contains the average body and brain measurements of five
primates.
reference:
P. J. Rousseeuw  and A. M. Leroy (1987) Robust Regression and
Outlier Detection. Wiley, p. 57.
